WEBVTT

1
00:01:13.814 --> 00:01:19.945
In my life, I've only painted
the honest expression of myself.


2
00:01:22.114 --> 00:01:25.993
To say what I
couldn't in any other way.

3
00:01:28.913 --> 00:01:32.416
I paint because I need to.

4
00:03:37.541 --> 00:03:41.337
Who would've thought
that stains of color can come to life


5
00:03:41.420 --> 00:03:44.340
and help one live?

6
00:03:47.384 --> 00:03:52.014
Mexico was my entire universe.

7
00:03:53.974 --> 00:03:57.019
I was happy.

8
00:04:06.278 --> 00:04:10.449
I ran through every corner of my yard

9
00:04:11.116 --> 00:04:16.080
and I'd shout and
laugh from under a tree.

10
00:04:33.722 --> 00:04:36.892
My mom was obsessively religious.

11
00:04:37.893 --> 00:04:41.188
She invited priests to
hold Mass at my house


12
00:04:41.605 --> 00:04:45.567
and her friends would
come to pray the rosary.


13
00:04:46.694 --> 00:04:49.363
While everyone was praying

14
00:04:49.863 --> 00:04:53.575
I tried not to laugh.

15
00:04:57.121 --> 00:05:02.001
I remember asking about the
Mysteries of the Bible.


16
00:05:03.168 --> 00:05:10.134
They'd always say,
"To dedicate oneself more to God."


17
00:05:21.895 --> 00:05:26.275
But I kept bothering the priest
with questions.


18
00:05:27.901 --> 00:05:29.987
How was Christ born?

19
00:05:31.572 --> 00:05:35.200
Was the Virgin Mary really a virgin?

20
00:05:41.081 --> 00:05:45.252
They threw me out
for spoiling it for the other kids.


21
00:05:52.301 --> 00:05:54.678
My father was a photographer.

22
00:05:54.970 --> 00:05:58.766
I was fascinated with his studio.

23
00:06:00.392 --> 00:06:05.105
Papa was an atheist
and the only one in the house who read


24
00:06:05.773 --> 00:06:11.111
books about science,
geography, and history.


25
00:06:17.201 --> 00:06:20.537
I went everywhere with my father.

26
00:06:21.997 --> 00:06:25.793
He would paint small
landscapes by the river


27
00:06:26.752 --> 00:06:30.464
with watercolors and oil paints.

28
00:06:36.095 --> 00:06:42.476
Papa kept his box of paints
tucked away in his studio.


29
00:06:43.393 --> 00:06:48.148
And I really wanted that box.

30
00:06:52.778 --> 00:06:54.029
Green

31
00:06:54.613 --> 00:06:57.783
good warm light

32
00:06:59.159 --> 00:07:00.661
Magenta

33
00:07:01.370 --> 00:07:03.122
Aztec

34
00:07:04.540 --> 00:07:06.083
Mexican red

35
00:07:06.333 --> 00:07:09.044
old blood of the prickly pear

36
00:07:09.878 --> 00:07:11.255
Brown

37
00:07:11.672 --> 00:07:13.298
color of molé

38
00:07:14.007 --> 00:07:15.217
earth

39
00:07:16.927 --> 00:07:18.137
Yellow

40
00:07:19.012 --> 00:07:22.266
sun and happiness

41
00:07:30.149 --> 00:07:33.986
I was a girl who walked
through a world full of colors


42
00:07:34.486 --> 00:07:36.613
of tangible forms.

43
00:07:41.201 --> 00:07:44.079
Everything was mysterious
and held secrets.


44
00:07:55.257 --> 00:07:59.428
Deciphering the world was like a game.

45
00:08:21.783 --> 00:08:23.785
I wanted to be a doctor

46
00:08:24.912 --> 00:08:27.915
so I attended the National
Preparatory School.


47
00:08:32.711 --> 00:08:38.508
I didn't like it at first because
I had to go upstairs with the other girls.


48
00:08:39.968 --> 00:08:41.887
All the girls would say

49
00:08:42.179 --> 00:08:44.806
"Frida is a little strange."

50
00:08:48.310 --> 00:08:52.481
I ended up befriending a group called
the <i>Cachuchas.</i>


51
00:08:56.360 --> 00:08:58.153
We wore caps

52
00:08:58.278 --> 00:09:01.615
and I was the only girl.

53
00:09:11.291 --> 00:09:14.544
When Frida arrived
at the school she was rebellious


54
00:09:14.628 --> 00:09:17.714
and defied tradition.

55
00:09:20.342 --> 00:09:25.722
She was drawn to rebellious young men

56
00:09:26.348 --> 00:09:29.476
and she joined our group.

57
00:09:39.611 --> 00:09:42.864
I followed the <i>Cachuchas</i> everywhere

58
00:09:43.657 --> 00:09:47.953
and took part in all of their mischief.

59
00:09:57.546 --> 00:10:00.257
We strapped firecrackers on a dog

60
00:10:00.382 --> 00:10:02.926
and we sent it into the school.

61
00:10:04.928 --> 00:10:10.600
We wreaked havoc
and got all the classes suspended.


62
00:10:13.312 --> 00:10:18.525
Frida was standing in a hallway
dying of laughter.


63
00:10:24.114 --> 00:10:27.826
I would go to the boys' classes
instead of going to mine.


64
00:10:28.035 --> 00:10:30.203
I barely passed my classes

65
00:10:30.579 --> 00:10:33.415
or I would cheat to get good grades.

66
00:10:43.425 --> 00:10:46.428
Alejandro was a leader at school.

67
00:10:47.137 --> 00:10:51.433
He took part in all of
the student protests.


68
00:10:53.352 --> 00:10:57.356
I'm attracted to intelligent people.

69
00:10:57.898 --> 00:11:02.861
I choose those I
feel are superior to me.

70
00:11:04.404 --> 00:11:05.822
My Alex

71
00:11:06.823 --> 00:11:08.700
My beloved Alex

72
00:11:09.826 --> 00:11:11.203
My Alex

73
00:11:14.748 --> 00:11:17.459
I wanted Alejandro to fuck me

74
00:11:18.001 --> 00:11:20.253
but he preferred to tell me nice things.

75
00:11:20.545 --> 00:11:22.339
He'd recite poetry

76
00:11:22.422 --> 00:11:25.425
and give me kisses and hugs.

77
00:11:28.136 --> 00:11:31.848
I think that everything
that gives pleasure is good.


78
00:11:37.687 --> 00:11:40.148
Breath

79
00:11:40.732 --> 00:11:42.442
scent

80
00:11:43.193 --> 00:11:45.153
armpit

81
00:11:45.570 --> 00:11:47.406
love

82
00:11:48.657 --> 00:11:51.034
abyss

83
00:12:23.024 --> 00:12:27.279
That day I took a bus with Alejandro.

84
00:12:29.823 --> 00:12:34.703
I sat next to the handrail
and Alejandro sat next to me.


85
00:12:36.121 --> 00:12:40.083
Shortly after getting on the bus
the crash started.


86
00:12:42.919 --> 00:12:46.381
A trolley approached our bus slowly

87
00:12:47.048 --> 00:12:48.800
hitting us straight in the middle.

88
00:12:51.636 --> 00:12:55.557
The bus had a strange elasticity.

89
00:12:56.266 --> 00:12:58.935
It bent more and more.

90
00:12:59.769 --> 00:13:02.772
When it reached its breaking point

91
00:13:03.190 --> 00:13:05.358
it burst into a thousand pieces.

92
00:13:12.866 --> 00:13:14.493
It wasn't violent

93
00:13:16.536 --> 00:13:18.497
but silent.

94
00:13:18.747 --> 00:13:20.290
Slow.

95
00:13:21.208 --> 00:13:27.088
The handrail went through me
like a sword through a bull.


96
00:13:30.258 --> 00:13:33.512
It's a lie that one realizes the crash.

97
00:13:34.846 --> 00:13:37.098
A lie that one cries.

98
00:13:38.433 --> 00:13:41.561
I had no tears.

99
00:13:43.438 --> 00:13:48.693
I didn't understand
the kind of wounds I had suffered.


100
00:13:49.486 --> 00:13:53.532
I thought I came out unscathed.

101
00:13:59.913 --> 00:14:02.249
I ended up under the trolley.

102
00:14:04.417 --> 00:14:09.839
As soon as I was able to get up
I looked for Frida.


103
00:14:12.676 --> 00:14:18.265
Horrified, I realized that
a piece of iron had pierced her body.


104
00:14:19.516 --> 00:14:22.519
A man said, "We
need to take it out."

105
00:14:22.602 --> 00:14:26.648
He put his knee on Frida's body
and pulled it out.


106
00:14:30.026 --> 00:14:36.908
Frida screamed so loud
you couldn't hear the ambulance's siren.


107
00:14:39.119 --> 00:14:45.542
CRASH WRECKS BUS

108
00:14:49.170 --> 00:14:52.090
The doctors didn't think
they could save her.


109
00:15:09.065 --> 00:15:14.529
It will take a long time
for the fracture in my pelvis to mend


110
00:15:15.030 --> 00:15:18.033
and for the wounds
in my foot to heal.

111
00:15:22.037 --> 00:15:26.708
The doctor thinks
I will have to stay like this


112
00:15:27.626 --> 00:15:30.462
for three or four months.

113
00:15:39.804 --> 00:15:44.100
I now inhabit a world of pain

114
00:15:45.935 --> 00:15:48.229
transparent

115
00:15:48.605 --> 00:15:50.690
like ice.

116
00:15:51.191 --> 00:15:54.277
It no longer holds mystery.

117
00:16:07.165 --> 00:16:09.751
The crash destroyed me

118
00:16:10.126 --> 00:16:12.545
but at least Lady Death didn't take me.

119
00:16:16.633 --> 00:16:20.637
Everyone tells me not to despair

120
00:16:24.307 --> 00:16:28.812
but no one knows
what it's like for me

121
00:16:29.270 --> 00:16:34.776
having been free in the
streets all my life.


122
00:16:40.448 --> 00:16:45.662
I feel trapped by
the walls in my room.

123
00:16:46.621 --> 00:16:51.334
I'm alone with my soul.

124
00:17:00.176 --> 00:17:08.176
My mother devised a wooden contraption
where I could attach my papers.


125
00:17:10.228 --> 00:17:18.228
She also hung a mirror over my bed
so I could use myself as a model.


126
00:17:21.030 --> 00:17:24.242
I started painting portraits of my friends.

127
00:17:28.788 --> 00:17:30.540
Dear Agustín

128
00:17:31.040 --> 00:17:34.127
I painted your portrait with love.

129
00:17:37.547 --> 00:17:39.632
Beautiful Alicia

130
00:17:40.300 --> 00:17:45.305
I'm sending you all my love.
Your pal, Friducha.


131
00:17:47.515 --> 00:17:50.268
Miguel, little brother

132
00:17:50.852 --> 00:17:53.646
don't ever forget about <i>Cachucha</i>number 9

133
00:17:53.730 --> 00:17:55.857
Frida Kahlo.

134
00:17:57.400 --> 00:17:59.068
Alex

135
00:17:59.652 --> 00:18:02.197
this is so you don't forget me.

136
00:18:02.947 --> 00:18:05.492
Don't stop writing to me.

137
00:18:09.579 --> 00:18:12.040
Here is my portrait, Alex.

138
00:18:12.749 --> 00:18:15.835
It'll be at your
house in a few days.

139
00:18:16.836 --> 00:18:20.965
I beg you, hang it low

140
00:18:21.800 --> 00:18:26.513
so you can see it
as if you were looking straight at me.


141
00:18:53.957 --> 00:18:57.252
After a year in many casts

142
00:18:57.585 --> 00:19:03.258
I still felt very sore
and had little strength.


143
00:19:04.133 --> 00:19:12.133
But I want to be productive
with the health I have left.


144
00:19:24.445 --> 00:19:29.534
When the Revolution started
I was aware of what was happening.


145
00:19:31.286 --> 00:19:38.126
I was four when I witnessed Zapata's
peasant fight against the establishment.


146
00:19:43.131 --> 00:19:48.678
The peasants took up arms to seize
the bread that the rich denied them.


147
00:19:49.512 --> 00:19:51.764
Land and freedom.

148
00:19:56.227 --> 00:20:03.067
In Mexico, <i>coraje</i> means
becoming violent when you face injustice.


149
00:20:09.699 --> 00:20:12.952
I feel the pain of the oppressed.

150
00:20:13.494 --> 00:20:17.332
I feel the need to fight for them.

151
00:20:18.374 --> 00:20:23.212
That's why as soon as they allowed me
to walk after the accident


152
00:20:23.338 --> 00:20:26.257
I joined the Communist party.

153
00:20:33.723 --> 00:20:37.018
MEXICAN ART REFLECTS NEW VALUES

154
00:20:37.101 --> 00:20:40.688
ART AND REVOLUTION

155
00:20:57.664 --> 00:21:02.377
The spirit of the Revolution

156
00:21:02.794 --> 00:21:06.255
was the foundation for my determination.

157
00:21:28.945 --> 00:21:34.117
Diego Rivera was painting frescoes
at the Ministry of Education.


158
00:21:48.589 --> 00:21:50.633
Diego is a communist.

159
00:21:50.967 --> 00:21:56.264
His creative work is at the service of
the social revolution.


160
00:22:05.440 --> 00:22:07.442
He has great taste.

161
00:22:08.860 --> 00:22:12.280
He admires everything that emanates beauty

162
00:22:13.281 --> 00:22:18.870
whether it comes from
a woman or a mountain.


163
00:22:37.513 --> 00:22:42.685
I had only seen him from far away
but I admired him greatly.


164
00:22:44.145 --> 00:22:49.567
One day I brought him four paintings
and just like that I said


165
00:22:50.401 --> 00:22:52.904
"Diego! Get down!"

166
00:22:55.073 --> 00:23:00.453
I looked down from my
scaffold and saw a girl of about eighteen.


167
00:23:02.038 --> 00:23:06.167
She had a pretty
body and a delicate face.

168
00:23:08.961 --> 00:23:12.590
Look, I haven't come to flirt with you.

169
00:23:13.132 --> 00:23:17.595
Even though you're a womanizer
I've come to show you my paintings.


170
00:23:19.931 --> 00:23:24.393
If you're interested, let me know.
If not, that's fine.


171
00:23:24.602 --> 00:23:28.815
So I can find another
way to help my parents.


172
00:23:31.609 --> 00:23:34.570
I was impressed.

173
00:23:34.821 --> 00:23:39.158
Her canvases revealed
an unusual expressive energy.


174
00:23:39.367 --> 00:23:44.163
"In my opinion, you must continue
to paint," I said at once.


175
00:23:44.956 --> 00:23:48.584
He told me, "You have talent."

176
00:23:49.836 --> 00:23:53.714
That's when my courtship with Diego began.

177
00:24:17.446 --> 00:24:19.949
Diego is a big kid.

178
00:24:20.658 --> 00:24:24.412
His bulging eyes are never still

179
00:24:24.787 --> 00:24:29.125
as if they were made for a painter.

180
00:24:31.335 --> 00:24:39.335
His fleshy lips always show
a mischievous and tender smile.


181
00:24:41.846 --> 00:24:44.390
She got a kick
out of hearing him talk.

182
00:24:44.849 --> 00:24:50.354
She'd tease him and rile him up.

183
00:24:51.731 --> 00:24:54.442
I saw Diego had a new girl.

184
00:24:54.525 --> 00:24:56.944
She was quite a young lady.

185
00:24:58.029 --> 00:25:00.740
Almost at once, he
painted her into a mural.


186
00:25:02.992 --> 00:25:05.244
"You have a dog face," he told her.

187
00:25:05.328 --> 00:25:08.748
"And you," she retorted,
"have the face of a frog."


188
00:25:09.749 --> 00:25:11.069
Toad Face

189
00:25:11.125 --> 00:25:13.228
became her favorite name for him,

190
00:25:13.252 --> 00:25:15.087
varied with the epithet...

191
00:25:15.379 --> 00:25:16.659
Fatbelly

192
00:25:16.714 --> 00:25:18.734
and sometimes the tenderer...

193
00:25:18.758 --> 00:25:20.718
Little Diego

194
00:25:21.052 --> 00:25:25.431
Then he began
asking for her opinion of his own work.


195
00:25:25.514 --> 00:25:28.517
Her verdict was at times quite unfavorable.

196
00:25:29.602 --> 00:25:33.856
He would grumble, but the next day,
he would alter the offending detail.


197
00:25:38.861 --> 00:25:41.239
I used to dress like a boy.

198
00:25:44.450 --> 00:25:49.413
But when I started seeing Diego
I put on traditional Tehuana dresses.


199
00:26:04.262 --> 00:26:08.891
You will be called Auxochrome
the one who captures color.


200
00:26:09.558 --> 00:26:14.563
I, Chromophore, the one that gives color.

201
00:26:37.545 --> 00:26:41.716
DIEGO RIVERA IS MARRIED

202
00:26:42.842 --> 00:26:49.307
Everyone said it was like
marrying an elephant to a dove.


203
00:27:00.860 --> 00:27:03.446
I want to have a son

204
00:27:04.071 --> 00:27:07.158
because this is a man's world.

205
00:27:08.492 --> 00:27:11.078
I want him to look like Diego.

206
00:27:13.664 --> 00:27:18.794
If I were to have a girl
I would like her to look a bit like me


207
00:27:19.712 --> 00:27:21.714
but prettier.

208
00:27:30.723 --> 00:27:35.644
I would go to see Diego every day
while he painted.


209
00:27:36.645 --> 00:27:42.943
It pleased him to see me arrive
with food in a basket covered in flowers.


210
00:27:52.328 --> 00:27:56.123
I was working as much
as seven days a week

211
00:27:56.207 --> 00:28:00.753
and 18 hours a day on
government commissions.


212
00:28:04.548 --> 00:28:11.680
When an art dealer offered me a one-man show
at the Museum of Modern Art in New York


213
00:28:11.889 --> 00:28:14.183
I got incredibly excited.

214
00:28:15.434 --> 00:28:21.065
For an artist this is the pinnacle
of professional success.


215
00:28:33.953 --> 00:28:35.037
Here it is

216
00:28:35.704 --> 00:28:36.956
the might

217
00:28:37.790 --> 00:28:38.999
the power

218
00:28:39.875 --> 00:28:41.335
the glory

219
00:28:41.585 --> 00:28:43.838
the youthfulness of our lands.

220
00:28:48.968 --> 00:28:53.013
Noted
Mexican painter Diego Rivera has arrived.


221
00:28:54.306 --> 00:28:58.686
A petite, birdlike woman, Señora Rivera
smiled from behind her husband.


222
00:29:01.522 --> 00:29:04.233
New York is so massive

223
00:29:04.567 --> 00:29:08.279
I can't believe it was built by people.

224
00:29:11.574 --> 00:29:15.619
Our hotel is right
in front of Central Park

225
00:29:16.287 --> 00:29:19.290
only a block away from 5th Avenue.

226
00:29:31.051 --> 00:29:35.514
Some neighborhoods in New York
are much more interesting than ours.


227
00:29:39.268 --> 00:29:41.020
We went to Harlem.

228
00:29:41.437 --> 00:29:43.772
It's a beautiful thing to see.

229
00:29:51.489 --> 00:29:55.451
There are immigrant communities
from every part of the world.


230
00:29:58.704 --> 00:30:03.000
The celebrations in Chinatown
feel like the ones in Mexico.


231
00:30:03.709 --> 00:30:06.587
Full of fireworks and colors.

232
00:30:19.600 --> 00:30:22.645
We received a magnificent welcome

233
00:30:23.395 --> 00:30:27.566
and we were feted at parties,
dinners, and receptions.


234
00:30:28.150 --> 00:30:31.195
Diego is the big shit here.

235
00:30:32.696 --> 00:30:38.452
High society people lead
the most stupid lives.


236
00:30:39.995 --> 00:30:47.211
They all spout nonsense
and brag about their millions.


237
00:30:49.338 --> 00:30:52.591
You also need to own tons of dresses.

238
00:30:53.467 --> 00:30:58.597
If you show up looking disheveled
they will eat you alive.


239
00:31:01.934 --> 00:31:04.270
But Mexico is in style now

240
00:31:04.895 --> 00:31:08.399
and all of my dresses
catch their attention.


241
00:31:08.899 --> 00:31:11.026
Their jaws drop

242
00:31:12.278 --> 00:31:17.783
because they're a bunch of idiots
who get excited over the dumbest things.


243
00:31:28.419 --> 00:31:32.590
Diego is painting two
blocks from our hotel.


244
00:31:42.766 --> 00:31:45.561
I am also painting all the time.

245
00:31:47.855 --> 00:31:52.901
I paint things that are
heavily influenced by Diego.


246
00:31:57.656 --> 00:31:59.992
I've adapted to his style.

247
00:32:00.200 --> 00:32:03.037
I try my best to
make sure it's done well.

248
00:32:08.667 --> 00:32:10.895
She did small paintings with

249
00:32:10.919 --> 00:32:12.880
bright Mexican colors.

250
00:32:12.963 --> 00:32:16.300
But she did not ask
me to look at her work.

251
00:32:16.383 --> 00:32:18.927
She was a little shy about her painting.

252
00:32:20.471 --> 00:32:23.349
She didn't set herself up as an artist.

253
00:32:23.432 --> 00:32:26.935
She was there because
Diego Rivera was starring.


254
00:32:47.206 --> 00:32:50.584
