For the first time in my life
I sold one of my pieces.


501
01:01:31.261 --> 01:01:36.058
I now have a commission to paint
a self-portrait with monkeys.


502
01:01:37.226 --> 01:01:40.896
It seems that everyone wants monkeys.

503
01:01:41.105 --> 01:01:43.357
I don't know why.

504
01:01:58.997 --> 01:02:03.961
The Surrealist poet André Breton
came to Mexico.


505
01:02:07.089 --> 01:02:11.593
On my
arrival in Mexico, my eyes remained closed


506
01:02:11.677 --> 01:02:15.139
to the perfect nobility
and terrible poverty


507
01:02:15.222 --> 01:02:19.601
of the Indian people
in the sun-drenched marketplaces.


508
01:02:26.733 --> 01:02:29.695
I had not yet
set eyes on Frida Kahlo.

509
01:02:29.778 --> 01:02:35.367
Like a fairy-tale princess,
with magic spells at her fingertips.


510
01:02:39.955 --> 01:02:43.959
My surprise was unbounded when I discovered

511
01:02:44.042 --> 01:02:48.714
that her work had blossomed forth
into pure surreality


512
01:02:48.797 --> 01:02:53.886
despite the fact that it had been conceived
without any prior knowledge whatsoever


513
01:02:53.969 --> 01:02:59.266
of the ideas motivating the activities
of my friends and myself.


514
01:03:04.271 --> 01:03:06.815
I never knew I was a Surrealist

515
01:03:07.024 --> 01:03:11.862
until André Breton came to Mexico
and told me I was one.


516
01:03:13.822 --> 01:03:20.454
I must confess I didn't even know
that this art movement existed.


517
01:03:24.833 --> 01:03:29.838
Surrealism is
the omnipotence of dreams.


518
01:03:32.633 --> 01:03:35.636
We are privileged to be present

519
01:03:35.719 --> 01:03:40.641
at the entry of a young woman
endowed with all the gifts of seduction,


520
01:03:40.724 --> 01:03:45.479
one accustomed to the society
of men of genius.


521
01:03:45.562 --> 01:03:50.984
The art of Frida Kahlo
is a ribbon around a bomb.


522
01:04:04.331 --> 01:04:08.085
I adore surprises and the unexpected.

523
01:04:09.127 --> 01:04:11.755
But I never painted my dreams.

524
01:04:12.214 --> 01:04:15.842
I painted my own reality.

525
01:04:30.357 --> 01:04:38.357
Breton was so impressed with my work he
urged me to exhibit in Paris and New York.


526
01:04:53.463 --> 01:05:01.463
A Surrealist gallery in New York
invited me to do a solo exhibition.


527
01:05:03.932 --> 01:05:07.060
I've never had an exhibition before.

528
01:05:10.731 --> 01:05:13.501
The flutter
of the week in Manhattan was caused


529
01:05:13.525 --> 01:05:16.695
by the first exhibition of paintings
by Frida Kahlo.


530
01:05:16.778 --> 01:05:22.284
Little Frida's pictures had the playful
bloody fancy of an unsentimental child.


531
01:05:23.744 --> 01:05:26.622
Everything went wonderfully.

532
01:05:27.122 --> 01:05:31.084
I displayed 25 pieces and sold 12.

533
01:05:35.839 --> 01:05:40.677
From there I went to Paris for an
exhibition organized by André Breton.


534
01:05:55.525 --> 01:06:00.238
Ever since I arrived,
it's been a shit show.


535
01:06:01.281 --> 01:06:04.242
My exhibition wasn't even set up.

536
01:06:04.493 --> 01:06:08.997
My paintings were waiting patiently for me
in customs.


537
01:06:09.289 --> 01:06:14.878
The son-of-a-bitch Breton
hadn't even gone to pick them up.


538
01:06:16.713 --> 01:06:20.509
Now Breton wants to exhibit my paintings

539
01:06:20.842 --> 01:06:24.513
along with common objects
he bought in Mexican markets.


540
01:06:27.557 --> 01:06:29.184
Ordinary crap.

541
01:06:29.726 --> 01:06:31.395
It's all junk.

542
01:06:36.942 --> 01:06:41.488
The exhibition will finally open
at the Pierre Colle gallery.


543
01:06:41.571 --> 01:06:44.908
They say it's one
of the best ones here.

544
01:06:48.412 --> 01:06:52.624
There was quite a crowd at the opening.

545
01:06:54.084 --> 01:06:57.087
Huge congratulations from Joan Miró.

546
01:06:57.629 --> 01:07:00.882
Great praise from Kandinsky.

547
01:07:01.383 --> 01:07:06.763
And congratulations from Picasso
and other big <i>cacas</i> of Surrealism.


548
01:07:08.598 --> 01:07:14.438
But these rich bitches
don't want to buy anything.


549
01:07:16.773 --> 01:07:22.529
I don't have the honor of being
in the elite circle of famous artists.


550
01:07:23.321 --> 01:07:25.449
Men are kings.

551
01:07:25.866 --> 01:07:28.744
They rule the world.

552
01:07:37.043 --> 01:07:41.173
These people make me want to vomit.

553
01:07:42.340 --> 01:07:48.346
They sit in the cafés for hours
warming their precious asses.


554
01:07:48.513 --> 01:07:53.727
They talk endlessly about "culture"
"art" and "revolution."


555
01:07:54.394 --> 01:08:00.358
They poison the air
with theories that never come true.


556
01:08:03.570 --> 01:08:05.822
I hate Surrealism.

557
01:08:07.032 --> 01:08:11.745
It's a decadent manifestation
of bourgeois art.


558
01:08:18.251 --> 01:08:24.800
I am so sick of the whole affair.
To hell with everything.


559
01:08:25.675 --> 01:08:31.306
Fuck everything concerning Breton
and this lousy place.


560
01:08:31.848 --> 01:08:34.226
Let them eat shit.

561
01:08:34.392 --> 01:08:37.771
I am going home.

562
01:08:51.660 --> 01:08:54.246
I feel like hell.

563
01:08:55.455 --> 01:09:00.210
Exhausted by the constant pain in my back
that gets worse every day.


564
01:09:11.346 --> 01:09:16.142
I am fucked because of the accident.

565
01:09:19.813 --> 01:09:22.649
My foot always hurts.

566
01:09:23.942 --> 01:09:30.866
The nerves are damaged
and my foot will never be the same.


567
01:09:32.450 --> 01:09:34.661
It's hopeless.

568
01:09:42.460 --> 01:09:48.466
All the doctors want me
to have an operation.


569
01:09:50.552 --> 01:09:52.846
I'm scared.

570
01:10:02.355 --> 01:10:06.318
In the end, they proceeded to break bones.

571
01:10:07.611 --> 01:10:13.408
They tore off a piece of my pelvis
and fused it to my spine.


572
01:10:24.961 --> 01:10:30.133
The bone will take a long time
to grow and readjust.


573
01:10:31.343 --> 01:10:34.888
I'll have to stay in this hospital
for quite a while.


574
01:10:38.266 --> 01:10:42.020
It is hard to imagine my future.

575
01:10:42.562 --> 01:10:46.650
I can't think about
it until I get well.

576
01:10:49.486 --> 01:10:54.699
Tree of hope, stay strong.

577
01:11:16.346 --> 01:11:20.225
Frida, I haven't known how to say this.

578
01:11:20.725 --> 01:11:26.314
I've never been able to admit
how much I love you


579
01:11:26.940 --> 01:11:29.943
but now I'm sure of it.

580
01:11:31.611 --> 01:11:36.032
Little girl, I'm terribly worried
about your illness.


581
01:11:44.040 --> 01:11:50.296
He tells me I am the woman
he loves above everyone else


582
01:11:50.714 --> 01:11:55.301
and he wants me to marry him again.

583
01:11:58.179 --> 01:12:03.685
I loved her and I
begged her to marry me again


584
01:12:04.060 --> 01:12:06.354
but without success.

585
01:12:06.813 --> 01:12:11.776
When she finally accepted
she did so with conditions.


586
01:12:13.611 --> 01:12:18.742
That she would support herself
with the earnings of her own work.


587
01:12:19.659 --> 01:12:24.330
That I would only pay for half
of our home expenses.


588
01:12:25.123 --> 01:12:27.959
And that we wouldn't
have sex with each other.


589
01:12:29.294 --> 01:12:33.631
When explaining this
last condition, she said


590
01:12:34.424 --> 01:12:41.723
When I imagine you with all your
other women I can't make love to you.


591
01:12:42.265 --> 01:12:49.439
As soon as you start seducing me
I face a psychological barrier.


592
01:12:52.692 --> 01:12:57.572
I felt so happy to have her back
that I accepted all of her conditions.


593
01:12:57.989 --> 01:13:02.285
Frida and I got
married for a second time.

594
01:13:28.269 --> 01:13:30.438
Our second marriage is going well.

595
01:13:32.232 --> 01:13:38.530
There is more mutual understanding.
No more jealousy or violent arguments.


596
01:13:41.741 --> 01:13:46.704
Each spouse does their part
to maintain the home.


597
01:13:49.457 --> 01:13:52.502
We'll be together forever.

598
01:13:54.129 --> 01:13:57.173
Nothing but love between us.

599
01:14:12.397 --> 01:14:14.065
My little boy

600
01:14:14.482 --> 01:14:20.446
I will build you a home
with all of my love.


601
01:14:31.541 --> 01:14:35.211
I'm now teaching at an art school.

602
01:14:42.385 --> 01:14:46.431
And in the afternoons I dedicate myself
to the beauty of painting.


603
01:14:48.600 --> 01:14:55.773
As soon as I finish one I have to sell it to
earn enough money for the monthly expenses.


604
01:14:58.276 --> 01:15:00.653
If it weren't for my health

605
01:15:01.779 --> 01:15:04.616
you could even say that I'm happy.

606
01:15:23.468 --> 01:15:29.015
Up until 1950, 
I was doing well enough.

607
01:15:30.391 --> 01:15:33.561
But now my health is at its worst.

608
01:15:38.483 --> 01:15:42.403
Frida became a professional patient.

609
01:15:43.363 --> 01:15:46.699
She had many surgical interventions

610
01:15:47.075 --> 01:15:50.745
a parade of doctors and orthopedic braces.

611
01:15:51.496 --> 01:15:55.083
They would hang her to
straighten her spine.


612
01:16:02.006 --> 01:16:04.050
This is my reality.

613
01:16:04.550 --> 01:16:06.552
There is no remedy.

614
01:16:07.470 --> 01:16:11.307
Despite it all
nothing is better than laughter.


615
01:16:11.933 --> 01:16:16.104
Laughing hard gives you strength.

616
01:16:18.147 --> 01:16:22.485
At the
hospital, Frida made light of her pain


617
01:16:23.194 --> 01:16:26.114
and swore all the time.

618
01:16:26.781 --> 01:16:29.284
Fucking life.

619
01:16:33.204 --> 01:16:37.041
If she saw me with
a pretty woman, she'd say


620
01:16:37.250 --> 01:16:41.296
Pass her to me. 
I'll take a puff.

621
01:16:46.592 --> 01:16:48.970
I'm always in a cast

622
01:16:49.429 --> 01:16:51.472
but I'm not discouraged.

623
01:16:53.474 --> 01:16:56.644
I have an enormous will to live.

624
01:17:01.607 --> 01:17:04.444
Long live life!

625
01:17:28.634 --> 01:17:32.430
I'm sure they will amputate my right leg.

626
01:17:34.182 --> 01:17:39.187
I don't know the details
but my doctors are concerned.


627
01:17:59.665 --> 01:18:01.334
I'm an invalid.

628
01:18:04.462 --> 01:18:12.462
Now I am trapped
in this fucking house of oblivion.


629
01:18:17.809 --> 01:18:19.685
Yellow

630
01:18:21.020 --> 01:18:22.814
sickness

631
01:18:23.189 --> 01:18:24.941
fear

632
01:18:26.109 --> 01:18:30.780
All the ghosts wear this color.

633
01:18:33.533 --> 01:18:35.785
Red

634
01:18:37.745 --> 01:18:39.747
blood

635
01:18:46.504 --> 01:18:48.881
Black

636
01:18:51.259 --> 01:18:53.177
Nothing is black

637
01:18:55.221 --> 01:18:57.306
truly nothing.

638
01:19:07.150 --> 01:19:09.026
I want to die.

639
01:19:14.949 --> 01:19:18.786
After the operation to amputate her leg

640
01:19:19.245 --> 01:19:21.414
everything was silent.

641
01:19:22.623 --> 01:19:27.587
Not even Diego's presence helped
and she didn't want to paint at all.


642
01:19:28.254 --> 01:19:31.048
The doctor said
not to force her to do anything


643
01:19:31.132 --> 01:19:33.509
because she didn't want to live anymore.

644
01:19:37.597 --> 01:19:41.142
But one morning, she
looked up at me and said


645
01:19:41.893 --> 01:19:43.853
I think I'm going to paint.

646
01:19:45.396 --> 01:19:49.484
I had to bind her to her
wheelchair so she could sit up straight.


647
01:20:02.538 --> 01:20:05.249
In my life I've painted little

648
01:20:06.959 --> 01:20:11.005
without the slightest desire
for glory or ambition


649
01:20:13.341 --> 01:20:18.137
with the sole conviction
to give myself pleasure


650
01:20:20.473 --> 01:20:24.727
and the power to make
a living with my trade.


651
01:20:27.647 --> 01:20:32.902
I've lost so many things
I wanted for my life.


652
01:20:34.487 --> 01:20:38.366
But painting completed my life.

653
01:21:05.476 --> 01:21:12.817
I told Diego it was an outrage that we had
never held an exhibition for Frida in Mexico


654
01:21:13.526 --> 01:21:18.155
and what would he say about
holding one in my gallery.


655
01:21:19.699 --> 01:21:25.621
EXHIBITION OF FRIDA KAHLO'S
BODY OF WORK


656
01:21:33.963 --> 01:21:36.215
She arrived in an ambulance

657
01:21:36.799 --> 01:21:38.884
like a heroine.

658
01:21:41.887 --> 01:21:44.140
Frida sat in the middle of the room.

659
01:21:45.516 --> 01:21:51.522
She was pleased to see so many people
honoring her warmly.


660
01:21:56.068 --> 01:21:58.904
She said almost nothing.

661
01:22:00.573 --> 01:22:06.454
She must have realized
she was bidding life goodbye.


662
01:22:10.207 --> 01:22:12.668
I am not afraid of death.

663
01:22:14.211 --> 01:22:18.090
Even so, I must face the bitter fact

664
01:22:18.591 --> 01:22:22.928
that having many lives
would still not be enough


665
01:22:23.596 --> 01:22:27.767
for me to paint everything I want.

666
01:22:48.371 --> 01:22:50.498
What is joy?

667
01:22:52.083 --> 01:22:55.086
The creation born of discovery.

668
01:23:05.137 --> 01:23:09.934
The lonely deer wandered
very sad and very hurt


669
01:23:11.143 --> 01:23:14.522
until it found warmth and a home.

670
01:23:18.192 --> 01:23:23.114
When the deer returns
strong, happy and healed


671
01:23:24.031 --> 01:23:29.412
the wounds he now bears
will all have been erased.


672
01:23:37.503 --> 01:23:40.089
Thank you for giving me solace.

673
01:23:41.716 --> 01:23:47.138
In the deer's forest,
the sky is now clear.